ss the country.\", \"from\": 1012, \"to\": 1226, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1099, \"end\": 1108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 0.9999999936997028, \"rank\": 6.299093852192741e-09, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}, {\"begin\": 1188, \"end\": 1194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6999183439381028, \"rank\": 0.41605516856874314, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The last torch bearer in Marseille will climb on the roof of the Velodrome stadium on May 9 and the relay will end in Paris on July 26 with the lighting of the Olympic cauldron during the Games' opening ceremony along the Seine river.\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1462, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1253, \"end\": 1262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 0.9999999936997028, \"rank\": 6.299093852192741e-09, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}, {\"begin\": 1346, \"end\": 1351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.006500683052716e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1450, \"end\": 1455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999874944, \"rank\": 1.2136732600569325e-11, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers hope the opening ceremony, in which 160 boats carrying athletes from around t